  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated WASH, CCA &amp; DRR Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Women and children have access to safe drinking water and sanitation facilities
- increased awareness on importance of health ,hygiene and environmental sanitation
- increased participation of women in project initiatives
- strong coordination in rural municipalities level
- increased women resilience in DRR &amp; CC initiatives
-Develop and broadcast 3 PSAs through 5 radio station on local language and 8 episodes of radio programs will be developed. 
-support of 30 basic PPE 30 set, disinfectant equipment, personal Hygiene Kit and hand washing buckets with tap and soap.
-250 marginalised HHs i.e. Dalits, majhi, single women, elderly supported with food items for 15 days as per GoN standards during lockdown. 
-3 packs of sanitary pad to 1000 women to protect them from infection and maintain hygiene.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project intends to :
- Women including children have access to adequate safe drinking water, sanitation facilities and improved hygiene practices.
- Strengthening of women resilience implemented through local government with development plans

The COVID response activities focuses on promoting and establishing hygienic behaviours to prevent from the virus by instilling hand washing stations, providing safety kit, sanitary pads for women and girls, disinfection equipment and personal hyenine kit for quarantine. The response is also focused on communicating the necessary information around COVID to make people aware and prevent from the virus. It also seeks to ensure the food security of marginalised HHs by supporting them with basic food items.</narrative>
  </description>
